                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Applied Math. and Computational Math. Individual "
                    }
                ],
                "level": 1
            },
            "bbox": [
                198,
                158,
                796,
                204
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Please solve as many problems as you can! "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                275,
                209,
                721,
                229
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "1. (20 pts) Ming Antu (1692-1763) is one of the greatest Chinese/Mongolian mathematicians. In the 1730s, he first established and used what was later to be known as Catalan numbers (Euler (1707-1763) rediscovered them around 1756; Belgian mathematician Eugene Catalan (1814- 1894) “rediscovered” them again in 1838), "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                193,
                275,
                836,
                360
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "c _ {n} = \\frac {1}{n + 1} \\binom {2 n} {n}, \\quad n = 0, 1, 2, \\dots",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/1a0608f9009f8cf97115ba79d208f4c39898b2d7423de99d0a63ea7ee37c7f02.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                347,
                367,
                645,
                404
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "and Ming Antu derived the following half-angle formula in 1730: "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                193,
                410,
                754,
                428
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "\\sin^ {2} \\frac {\\theta}{2} = \\sum_ {n = 1} ^ {\\infty} c _ {n - 1} \\left(\\frac {\\sin \\theta}{2}\\right) ^ {2 n}",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/4ed2fdd6cc32252e88518c7d2175000251cc467d1ff459bea706bf249dbd4b69.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                376,
                434,
                618,
                478
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Prove this formula. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                194,
                485,
                363,
                500
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Hint: you may use generating function "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                215,
                520,
                554,
                536
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "F (z) = \\sum_ {n = 0} ^ {\\infty} c _ {n} z ^ {n}",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/4a2e9475f315fd362ea5ba6a0a6dfb677c2d0453ea931164a24f60c18cb5bb15.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                426,
                544,
                569,
                588
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "and show that "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\begin{array} { r } { \\sum _ { m + k = n } c _ { m } c _ { k } = c _ { n + 1 } } \\end{array}"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "and then show "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "z F ( z ) ^ { 2 } = F ( z ) - 1"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                194,
                594,
                796,
                614
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "2. Many algorithms, including polynomial factorisation in finite fields, require to compute gc "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\operatorname { d } ( f ( X ) , X ^ { N } - 1 )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "for a polynomial "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "f"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "of reasonably small degree n and a binomial "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "X ^ { N } - 1"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "of very large degree "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "N"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". Since "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "N"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is very large the direct application of the Euclid algorithm is very inefficient. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                193,
                621,
                803,
                705
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Questions: "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                213,
                722,
                309,
                739
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "list",
            "content": {
                "list_type": "text_list",
                "list_items": [
                    {
                        "item_type": "text",
                        "item_content": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "(i) (10 pts) Suggest a more efficient approach the direct computation of "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "\\operatorname* { g c d } ( f ( X ) , X ^ { N } - 1 )"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "via the Euclid algorithm. "
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "item_type": "text",
                        "item_content": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "(ii) (10 pts) Generalise it to "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "\\operatorname* { g c d } ( f ( X ) , A _ { 1 } X ^ { N _ { 1 } } + . . . + A _ { m } X ^ { N _ { m } } +"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "A _ { m + 1 }"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "). "
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                221,
                744,
                800,
                809
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Hint: If for three polynomials "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "f"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "g"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "and "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "h"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "we have "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "g \\equiv h"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "(mod "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "f"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ") then "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                194,
                833,
                801,
                865
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "\\operatorname * {g c d} (f, g) = \\operatorname * {g c d} (f, h).",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/117b3030cfa0aa320194528457c6e91fbd5d6adbd89407f133d5c8449261e4b7.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                403,
                869,
                591,
                888
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "page_header",
            "content": {
                "page_header_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "S.-T. Yau College Student Mathematics Contests 2014 "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                258,
                136,
